# SVG, pan capture, and click-vs-pan

## Coordinate transforms

Use `useMapTransform`'s `screenToSvg(clientX, clientY)`. Internally it uses `svg.getScreenCTM().inverse()` to convert client pixels into SVG viewBox coordinates, then undoes the inner `<g>` transform. **Do not** roll your own conversion from `containerRef.getBoundingClientRect()` - it ignores `preserveAspectRatio` and breaks when the SVG is letterboxed.

## SVG layout

Keep the outer `<svg>` on **`preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"`** always. Do **not** toggle `xMidYMin` / `xMidYMid` for overlays — that changes the CTM and breaks pan/zoom state.

`BuildingDrawer` uses the same **left** sheet on all breakpoints; `MapDisplay` / `MapPreview` pass `selectedId={selected?.id ?? null}` so map selection matches the open drawer.

## Pan capture pitfall (very important)

The canvas container has `data-pan="true"`. Its `onPointerDown` handler calls `node.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId)` for **any** press inside it - including children like buttons or polygons. Once captured, the matching `pointerup` is delivered to the container, and Chromium then refuses to fire a `click` on the original child target.

Fix: stop propagation at the child:

```tsx
// On any clickable child inside the panning container:
<polygon
  onPointerDown={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}
  onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); onClick(); }}
/>

// On floating control overlays:
<div onPointerDown={(e) => e.stopPropagation()} onPointerUp={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}>
  ...buttons
</div>
```

Already applied in: `MapOverlay` polygons, `EditorCanvas` polygons / handles, `MapControls`. Apply the same pattern when adding new clickable overlays.

## Right-click

Context menu is suppressed at both the container and the SVG level via `onContextMenu={(e) => e.preventDefault()}`. Right-click is **not** a pan trigger.

## Pinch / pan refs

`onPointerMove` reads `panState.current` / `pinchState.current` synchronously into local `const`s before calling `setViewState` - the setter runs asynchronously and the refs can become null between read and use. Don't dereference these refs inside the `setViewState` updater.
